comments.body:
nit: would it be more idiomatic to use `has_value()` here?
```suggestion
    const T& value() const LIFETIMEBOUND { assert(has_value()); return m_value; }
    T& value() LIFETIMEBOUND { assert(has_value()); return m_value; }
```

